SIMPLE: peculium
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peculium
<hw>Pe*cu"li*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Peculiar</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Law)</fld> <def>The
saving of a son or a slave with the father's or master's consent; a
little property or stock of one's own; any exclusive personal or
separate property.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A special fund for private and personal
uses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A slight <qex>peculium</qex> only subtracted to supply his snuff
box and tobacco pouch.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pecunial</ent>⟦br⟧
